Ongoing collection of links: 

* http://withhiddennoise.net/roussel/ : The original french poem, online version with parentheses that can be clicked to or hide the parenthesized text. 
* http://www.rousselnia.fr/ : Two interactive versions of the  version of the original french poem: A "linear" and a "topographic" one, and a separate page for browsing all 59 illustrations with the lines in whose context each appears (possibly the original texts given to the illustrator Henri-A. Zo, who according to the [[review of Ian Monks translation|http://madinkbeard.com/archives/new-impressions-of-africa-by-raymond-roussel]] was hired by detective and [[did not get to read the entire text of the poem|Illustration constraint of Nouvelles Impressions]]).
* http://press.princeton.edu/chapters/i9413.pdf : Introduction to the english translation of the work. 
* http://madinkbeard.com/archives/new-impressions-of-africa-by-raymond-roussel : Review of an english translation by Ian Monk, 2004.
* http://wordswithoutborders.org/book-review/raymond-roussels-impressions-of-africa : Review of an english translation by Mark Polizzotti, 2011.
